testing. Pt with L PF strength 2/5 (able to complete partial available ROM with resistance in seated position.)
Justification for Continued Skilled Services
Impairments Remaining Impairments: ankle weakness, impaired balance, impaired gait quality, poor righting reactions in NBOS
conditions.
Continued Skill Reason for Skilled Services: Pt reporting legs feel sluggish, and don't want to move sometimes. Pt noted to present
with poor ankle righting reactions in narrow stance conditions, presenting as a concern for potential falls when
navigating apartment and community. Pt additionally presenting this date with decreased MMT strength in B ankle PF
And DF. Pt with L DF MMT 3+/5, difficulty consistently clearing toes during swing phase of gait. R DF MMT 4+/5. Pt
participates in L ankle PF strength testing. Pt with L PF strength 2/5 (able to complete partial available ROM with
resistance in seated position.)
During the upcoming treatment period, physical therapy will focus on B ankle strength, balance retraining via
improved ankle righting reactions in narrow stance conditions in order to improve leg strength, agility, and safety
when navigating community.
Pt would greatly benefit from continued skilled PT to address remaining deficts and improve strength and safety when
navigating home and community.
