MRN: 5494
Precautions / Prior Living / Discharge / Transition Plan
Medical Hx Prior Medical History: 74 y/o patient admitted to St. Andrews Village for long term care from rehab at Center at Lowry.
She was found down at home x4 days, underwent SDH evacuation. Reports no memory of the fall and states she had
been using a walker recently, but not having significant mobility difficulty. Hospital notes not available to me, but prior
SNF notes indicate sepsis, diverticulitis bacteremia. Does report some history of a fall down her basement stairs,
which resulted in a spinal fusion L1-2 2019 and another fall in 2022, resulting in T11/12 fusion. C/o severe bilateral
foot pain r/t neuropathy as well as knee pain. States that her bilateral TKAs, completed 2018, had not previously
caused her any issues.
After two months of consistent participation in PT/OT, Flo demonstrates ability to transfer to ALF, but is still hopeful to
return to her home with community support. She will be able to use her wheelchair in the kitchen, but not the rest of
the home. She will require a level of modified independence with bed mobility, transfers, and ambulation at least 50'
increments including in and out of bathrooms.
Prior Living Prior Living Environment = Patient resided in private residence.
Prior Living Description: Pt lived in single story home with basement.
Prior Assistance Prior Cognitive Assistance = No supervision required
Prior Equipment Equipment Prior to Onset: Intermittent use of FWW
Discharge Plan Transition/Discharge Plan = Patient to live alone in private residence.
