attending activities more frequently. However, her activity tolerance continues to be severely impacted by OA in BIL
knees which limits pt's WBing tolerance and increases her fall risk with transfers. The pt's primary goal is to return to
ambulation for short distances but she is unable to achieve this due to knee pain. PT is currently working with PCP to
refer pt to orthopedics for cortisone injections for initial pain management. The pt requires continued skilled PT care
due to sedentary lifestyle at high risk for decline without structured therapy to encourage modified activity.
