--- Interventions

Aide: Activity: Ambulate patient using assistive device her four-wheeled walker or her wheelchair.

Aide: Activity: Assist with transfers using wheelchair.

Aide: Activity: Up in chair/wheelchair

Aide: Elimination: Assist to BSC/toilet using SBA and /or 4 wheel walker or wheelchair.

Aide: Hygiene: Assist patient with dressing as needed

Aide: Hygiene: Bath: Shower

Aide: Hygiene: Foot care - wash and apply lotion to feet as needed, avoid area between the toes in order to
prevent bacterial and fungal growth.

Aide: Hygiene: Shampoo prn, if bedbound,: may use shampoo cap or inflatable bedside basin for bedridden
patient. Temperature check shampoo cap when removed from microwave before application.

Aide: Hygiene: Skin care - Apply moisturizing lotion/cream to skin.

Aide: Safety: Fall precautions, pt has history of falls or is at high risk for falls. Reinforce fall precautions:
encourage pt to ambulate with assistance/assistive devices as needed, wear skid resistant footwear when
ambulating, keep walkways/hallways cleared of clutter or throw rugs, etc. Report to RN/LPN asap if pt has
a fall or reports a recent fall.

Aide: Safety: Oxygen precautions. Pt is on 3 to 5 liters per minute via NC continuously/PRN. Reinforce no
smoking or open flames around oxygen. Use non-petroleum based products on lips, face or upper chest.
Alert RN/LPN asap if pt is having any issues complying with oxygen safety, or pt has any concerns
questions regarding oxygen therapy.

Chaplain: Provide spiritual support and assistance to patient and family as needed

MSW: Assess final arrangements and end of life planning status

MSW: Assess patient's coping skills/behavior

MSW: Assess patient's psychosocial status including mental status and orientation

SN: Assess cognitive status for sensory limitations, impairments

SN: Assess current medications including: new/changed medications, side effects, and interactions

SN: Assess for history of falls and/or injury

SN: Assess for musculoskeletal deficits that may increase potential of falling

SN: Assess for presence of risk factors for infection

SN: Assess for signs/symptoms of depression

SN: Assess for signs/symptoms of urinary tract infection

SN: Assess measures in place to reduce risk and avoid urinary tract infection

SN: Assess patient's use of oxygen and oxygen effectiveness

SN: Assess respiratory status including rate, pattern, secretions, and lung sounds

SN: Instruct family/CG’s to call MEHH office for on call RN after every fall and not call 911. Educate re ER
visits or hospitalization may result in discharge from hospice care or pt could be responsible for ER/hospital
payment if MEHH did not approve the ER or hospitalization.

SN: Instruct patient/caregiver on safety awareness and safety measures

SN: Teach patient/caregiver measures to reduce risk and avoid urinary tract infection

SN: Teach patient/caregiver regarding oxygen therapy

SN: Teach patient/caregiver regarding s/s of respiratory infection and what to report

SN: Teach regarding activities and energy management

SN: Teach regarding the contents and use of the comfort pack

Goals:

Aide: Pt will be free from falls; Target Date: 3/4/2026

Aide; Patient's personal care needs will be met; Target Date: 3/4/2026

Aide: Maintains clean, safe environment; Target Date: 3/4/2026

Chaplain: Patient /caregiver will feel needs are being met as they have defined; Target Date: 3/4/2026
MSW: Patient will be able to express fears, anxieties, concerns ; Target Date: 3/4/2026

MSW: Patient will consult with staff as needed for support ; Target Date: 3/4/2026

 

