Assessment and Summary of Skilled Services
Interventions Skilled Interventions Provided: Strength, endurance, and mobility exercise to improve activity tolerance, safety, and
functional independence. Balance and coordination training to improve dual tasking, reactive balance strategies, and
reduce fall risk. Gait training to improve walking tolerance and safety with ambulation.
Patient Progress Progress & Response to Treatment: Pt is making good progress w/ treatment. He increased 30sSTS from 2 to 4 with
modification of BUE support but did demonstrate poor control with descent to sitting. Pt also improved 2MWT
distance from 22 to 54 meters, nearly reaching his STG and demonstrating improved gait quality with reduced
shuffling and improved gait speed. He did desaturate significantly with ambulation but recovered quickly. The pt
reports that he does not want to continue therapy but would benefit from 3-4 additional sessions to improve
mechanics with sit>stand and increase walking tolerance for facility distances so pt can safely complete transfers and
ambulate to and from dining room.
Balance Patient sits unsupported for 30 seconds with feet flat on floor and no back support? = Yes; Patient stands
unsupported with AD for 10 seconds? = No
Purpose Purpose of Exercise = Endurance,Strength
Communication Team Communication/Collaboration: Communication btw therapy disciplines, PCP, and pt's family to coordinate care
approaches and address all deficits.
