facilitate dynamic standing balance, facilitate independence with ADLs, improve rehab potential, increase functional
activity tolerance, increase safety awareness and maximize rehab potential in order to facilitate ability to live in
environment with least amount of supervision and assistance . Due to the documented physical impairments and
associated functional deficits, without skilled therapeutic intervention, the patient is at risk for: depression,
dehydration, DVT, falls, further decline in function, immobility, decreased skin integrity and decreased ability to return
