weight-shifting in transferring into/out of recliner chair in apartment, w/ assessment of 5xSTS w/ performance at
22.09s w/ BUE support; >16 seconds: Indicates a risk of falls. Generalized balance strategies have improved based
on BERG balance assessment progressing toward moderate to high to moderate to low fall risk w/ current
performance at 34/56; fall risk. PT care team has been coordinating w/ recommendation for referral placement to
orthotist company d/t LLD causing notable gait and functional mobility dysfunction w/ knee pain aspects in R knee,
albeit, minor, PT suspects pt to benefit from further skilled rehab and w/ assistance from proper orthotic in improving
pt's biomechanical functional mobility efficiencies and decreasing likelihood of chronic pain w/ augmented concerns in
fall risk. Pt remains motivated and willing for good participation in skilled physical therapy services.
