all household and facility navigation and is no longer requiring caregiver support at night, previously requiring 24/7
care. The pt is showing improved walking tolerance for facility and short community distances, working toward return
to PLOF. She continues to demonstrate increased deconditioning with more rapid fatigue compared to PLOF and still
requires caregiver assist during the day, which she did not have prior to her hip dislocation. The pt requires continued
skilled PT care to promote full return to PLOF and reduced reliance on caregiver support.
