Justification for Continued Skilled Services
Continued Skill Reason for Skilled Services: Pt continues to present with limitations and impairments indicating need for continued
skilled PT services. During stand > sit transfers, pt unable to initiate reaching for chair, noted to sit in chair with poor
eccentric control. Additionally, pt with limited safety awareness when completing stand-pivot transfers. This date, pt
requires Min A and 100% sequencing cues to safely complete transfer. Plan to focus skilled therapy on safety during
transfers, safe sequencing of transfer tasks, and LE strength to promote improved control during functional transfers.
Intervention Modes Can interventions be provided using treatment modes other than individual? = Yes; Will multiple modes provide a
value-added benefit? = Yes; Will multiple modes enhance the therapeutic experience? = Yes; Is patient agreeable to
modes other than individual? = Yes; Modes recommended = Group,Concurrent,Co-treatment; Maximum number of
patients for any group = Select All; Justification for group recommendation: Patient will benefit from group therapy as
an adjunct to individual therapy because group therapy will strengthen the patient’s ability to physically adapt to
environmental demands to improve safety, because group therapy will strengthen the patient’s ability to physically
respond to environmental cues which will decrease the risks when returning to a community setting and because
patient’s comprehension and insight of task demands will be enhanced by observing others’ activity.; Justification for
concurrent recommendation: Patient will benefit from concurrent therapy as an adjunct to individual therapy because
concurrent therapy will improve patient’s awareness and insight into condition, because concurrent therapy will
increase patient’s insight into condition and function through real-life activity that occurs in peer
interactions/observation and interaction with others and because concurrent therapy will provide a venue to challenge
the patient’s capacity to maintain safety while responding to attentional demands.; Justification for co-treatment
recommendation: Patient will benefit from co-treatment mode of therapy as an adjunct to individual therapy because
co-treatment will provide a venue where patient’s capacity for responding to functional progression and attentional
demands will improve, because patient’s comprehension and insight of task demands is enhanced with skills of a
second therapist and because patient's condition requires a second therapist to promote highest level of safey and
improvement with patient's current function.
