Assessment Summary Since Last Progress Report
Skill Skilled Interventions Provided: Therapeutic exercise: therapeutic exercises for BLE's to improve strength and
endurance for functional mobility and functional tasks. Neuromuscular Re-Ed: postural control, crossing midline,
hbalance strategies, static and dynamic balance to improve dynamic and static balance while standing and sitting.
Therapeutics activities: transfer training, and functional mobility tasks to improve activity tolerance and safety. Gait
Training: AD use and sequence, cognitive tasks, head turns, stepping and balance strategies, and instruction for
proper body mechanics to improve safety when ambulating in open environments while in the community and facility.
Manual therapy: soft tissue mobilization, PROM, and stretching to improve ROM and reduce pain/discomfort, edema,
and joint effusion. Vital assessment to determine appropriate exercise intensity and regiment.
