to navigate 5 stairs in a community setting without requiring assist from her family, which was a major achievement
for her. The pt also showed an improvement in upper body strength but continues to have restriction in lat and upper
trap BIL which affects shoulder ROM and ability to achieve required positioning for CT scans for cancer screening
without assist. She also demonstrates unsteadiness w/ NBOS and eyes closed. The pt requires continued skilled PT
care to minimize fall risk and improve functional strength and mobility for return to PLOF.
