adverse behaviors make choices about clothing, foods and activities, participate in activities of choice, follow
directions for activities and ADLs, plan for future events and reminisce about past, decrease risk for falls, enhance (I)
on nursing unit, improve ability to utilize visual aides, increase safety during ambulation, perform functional and/or
vocational tasks and participate in functional activities of choice.
Risk Factors Risk Factors: Due to the documented physical impairments and associated functional deficits, without skilled
therapeutic intervention, the patient is at risk for: Decreased ability to return to prior level of supervision, Falls and
