Assessment
Impressions Clinical Impressions: Donna demonstrates impaired balance, reduced lower extremity strength (LE MMT 4/5), and
decreased endurance (6MWT: 225 meters). Her TUG (16 seconds), 5xSTS (13 seconds), and SLS (1 second) all
indicate elevated fall risk. Berg Balance Score of 42/56 is below normative levels, with specific deficits in dynamic
balance tasks. Her cognitive impairment, history of falls, and chronic conditions (including heart failure and
osteoporosis) compound her mobility challenges. She requires skilled PT to address these multifactorial deficits and
prevent further decline or injury.
Skilled Need Skilled Justification: Donna requires skilled, medically necessary rehabilitation services due to her complex medical
history, cognitive impairment, and demonstrated functional deficits. Her elevated fall risk, impaired balance, and
reduced endurance necessitate skilled assessment and intervention to ensure safety and promote independence. PT
will focus on improving strength, balance, and functional mobility, with close monitoring due to her evolving clinical
presentation and comorbidities.
