Assessment Summary Since Last Progress Report
Precautions Precautions: Confusion, dementia, anxious. Does best with yes/no questions. Low back pain. Does not use walker for
gait.
Skill Skilled Interventions Provided: PT focued on manual therpay to help with muscle trigger point release, muscle
inhibition, stretching, strengthening, body mechanics, motor planning, joint mobalization, balance and endurance for
ADL tasks
Assessment Summary Since Eval/SOC
Response to Tx Progress & Response to Tx: Elder, staff and family report increased participation to 2-3 activities daily, she has joined
walking group with ability to do half lap around building and goal to do full lap. She has to sit for most of daily exercise
class but does it and reports no increaed pain 3/5 days. Her imapired cognition and impulsive nature leads to difficulty
some days with attention to task and correct body mechanics but with PT high repitiions on correct body mechanics
we are seeing improved carry over when outside PT. she is doing some self directed light jogging and has started
lifting weights in exercises class for improved quality of life.
