Initial Assessment / Current Level of Function & Underlying Impairments
Patient Referral and History
Hx/Complexities Current Hx/Problem: Patient reports that he has has fallen several times this year. He feels his balance is declining.
He uses a SPC outside his apartment. He uses a FWW at night to go to the bathroom. He uses the walker if he is
going outside but uses the cane to meals. He reports that his neck continues to bother him especially when looking
down. He states that his pain has moved from the back of his neck to the front (points to the SCM region). He had 4
injections to his neck and it didn't help. They are now recommending he have dry needling to the muscles but he
hasn't found anyone who does it yet.
Per his POA/daughter - patient's cognition has been declining recently and they thought it was a result of muscle
relaxant but he stopped taking that a week ago and still seems confused. She is wondering if he should use a walker
all the time as he seems more steady when pushing his wife in the wheelchair.
