Impressions Clinical Impressions: Patient presents with instability in gait, LE weakness and ROM deficits on RLE, pain in RLE
from the hip to the foot, and low back pain that interferes with the patient’s mobility and functional independence and
places him at high risk for falls. Patient has a history of falls with no injuries from the falls and states the most difficulty
he has is in gait, static standing, and changing positions. Patient demonstrates 29/56 on the Berg Balance Scale
indicating high risk for falls, 27 seconds on the TUG with 4WW and CGA indicating high risk for falls, and
demonstrates fatigue and shortness of breath after walking 20 ft. Patient has reduced stride length bilaterally, reduced
hip extension in terminal stance, reduced toe off in terminal stance, and anterior trunk lean with instability in SL
phase.
Skilled Need Skilled Justification: Skilled therapy services are required to place patient on a skilled maintenance plan to reduce risk
of functional decline with discharge, maximize functional outcomes, and reduce fall risk. Patient is unable to
implement an HEP that will assist the patient with maintaining functional decline due to memory deficits and lack of
caregiver to assist in implementation of HEP. Patient requires skilled services for max education, balance training to
reduce risk of falls, and gait training to maintain functional mobility. Patient also requires skilled therapy services for
pain management and strengthening of BLE. Without skilled therapy services the patient demonstrates consistent
functional decline reducing his community participation, walking abilities/tolerance/safety, and functional
independence.
