Patient Referral and History
Current Referral Reason for Referral / Current Illness: Pt is a 95 year old female who presents to skilled PT with complaints of decline
in strength, and difficulty completing funcitonal transfers.
On evaluation, pt presents with decreased BLE strength, B hip flexion MMT 3+/5, inability to ambulate >70 feet
without seated rest break, and inability to complete >1 STS consecutively. On 11/6/25, pt was able to complete
5XSTS assessment in 42 seconds, demonstrating a significant functional decline.
Patient demonstrates impaired cognition and decreased ability to follow a structured home exercise program
independently. Due to memory deficits, impaired safety awareness, and difficulty with motor planning, she is unable to
maintain strength or functional mobility without skilled cueing, supervision, and exercise progression provided in PT.
Pt would benefit from skilled PT 3x/week for 4 weeks to address the above listed impairments and return to baseline
level of functioning within AL.
