walk, he took a few steps, and froze. She states that they were able to get him sitting down in his wheelchair and
brought him back to their apartment in memory care where she lives with him. She states she took his blood pressure
and it was “about 60/40”. She states she notified the memory care staff and they called EMS. She states EMS
assessed him and sent him to the hospital. She states he was in the hospital for several days and while there they
