Initial Assessment / Current Level of Function & Underlying Impairments
Patient Referral and History
Current Referral Referred By = Primary Physician
Reason for Referral: Patient has increased difficulty with performing transfers, especially sit to stand and stand pivot
transfers. Patient requires increased assistance for transfers and she feels it is limiting her abilities. Patient has
instability walking, BLE weakness, impaired safety awareness, and poor activity tolerance.
Hx/Complexities Current Hx/Problem: Patient has progressive weakness, difficulty with sit to stand transfers, difficulty with gait, and
poor tolerance to activity that has been progressively worsening for a number of years. Patient has low tolerance to
activity and weakness in BLE that limits her ability to perform daily tasks independently.
Prior Medical History: Patient has a previous medical history of Parkinson’s disease, peripheral neuropathy, diabetes,
dysphasia, HLD, impaired mobility, and frequent falls, and patient is wheelchair bound.
