Assessment Summary Since Last Progress Report
Skill Skilled Interventions Provided: Patient seen 1x/wk for PT treatment this period (as requested by family) including: LE
AROM and ARROM exercises for improved strength and function, LE and trunk stretches to help with stiffness and
improve alignment of LEs in standing and transfers. Limited gait training with walker for safe mobility and transfers
with assist using walker. Transfer training to and from chair, bed and w/c with and without walker using gait belt. Bed
mobility training for improved ability to assist in movement with setup and help. W/C mobility training with use of UEs
and LEs for self mobility and better independence when in chair. Standing balance and endurance training at walker
for safe standing activity and care.
Assessment Summary Since Eval/SOC
Response to Tx Progress & Response to Tx: Patient has participated well 1x/wk (as requested by daughter) and has not c/o any
significant pain during treatment with gentle activities, but shows limited interest in regaining lost abilities and is
instead more interested in maintaining abilities and preventing decline. As daughter has requested we see her no
more than 1x/wk and limit activities involving walking or heavy resistance. I will update POC and change goals for
maintenance program to include: maintaining her CLOF to allow her to participate in mobility and care as best she
can, allow her to stand safely at a walker or grab bar, and propel w/c in hallway and room when needed.
