Patient Referral and History
Current Referral Reason for Referral: Patient referred to PT for pain and weakness following streptococcal infection.
Hx/Complexities Current Hx/Problem: Patient states he had a streptococcal infection in his lower two vertebrae that manifested as
muscle spasms in the torso, low back, and right buttock and leg in August 2025. States he went to the hospital and
they told him he just pulled a muslce in his back. States he came back to MorningStar (were he moved to in May
2025) and one day in the dining room he couldn’t move his right leg. States he went back to the hospital and they
diagnosed him with a streptococcal infection in his back. States he went to a rehab center after he was in the hospital
and then recivied home home upon his return to MorningStar. States he was using a walker due to pain and
weakness, though this week he is has advanced to using a walking stick.
States now he is getting pains in his right medial knee. States he can walk halfway around Morningstar before he
needs to sit down due to knee pain and buckling. States crossing his right leg in a piriformis type stretch relieves his
pain significantly. States he has difficulty going up stairs leading with the RLE. Patient states that he has a valve issue
that may need to be repaired (next year) and is having a cardioversion done next week. Patient states he has
difficulty with curb steps and going up steps at his children’s house.
Patient reports he is additionally experiencing right cervical radiculopathy that is radiating down into his left hand,
states he feels it most at night. Patient states he would like to focus on lower body deficits at this time.
