Initial Assessment / Current Level of Function & Underlying Impairments
Objective Tests and Measures
GDS Score Interpretation: PT administered brief cognitive rating scale and global detoriation scale (GDS), with pt receiving
a score of 5 on GDS which is commensurate with a moderately severe cognitive decline and moderate dementia. PT
is no longer able to survive without some assistance, he demonstrates difficutly recalling major recent events and
difficulty recalling some specific aspects of life, difficulty with most aspects of orientation, demonstrating some ability
to refer to watch and calendar to help improve orientation in environment, and demonstrates concentration/attention
deficits. Pt does not require assistance with toileting or eating, but does occasionally need assistance in some areas
of daily living (i.e., choosing proper clothing, attending meals on time, navigating around ALF community, etc.)
Assessment Summary
Clinical Clinical Impressions: Pt presents with severe cognitive linguistic deficits, impacting overall safety, function,
Impressions independence and QOL in new living environment. Pt is often seen wandering around ALF community, demonstrating
significant short term memory and orientation deficits, relying significantly on ALF community staff, therapy team, or
peers in order to orientate.
Reason for Skilled Justification: Pt requires skilled ST services in order to improve functional cognitive linguistic skills necessary
Therapy to improve ability to effectively communicate wants/needs/ideas, improve short term memory and orientation, improve
safety/function in ADLs and daily routines, improve participation in activities of preference, and improve overall
independence and QOL in ALF living environment. Without participation in ST intervention, pt is at significant
increased risk of requiring higher level of care, likely needing memoy care.
Risk Factors Risk Factors: None noted.
Plan Focus Focus of Plan of Treatment = Restoration,Compensation,Adaptation
