Assessment Summary Since Last Progress Report
Precautions Precautions: fall risk
Skill Skilled Interventions Provided: OP PT skilled services provided since the last progress note have included:
therapeutic exercises progressing the patient's LE strength/endurance, gait training for improved gait technique and
confidence on even and uneven surfaces with the least restrictive assist device, exercises to challenge the patient's
standing balance and coordination, and therapeutic activities which have progressed the patient's stair climbing and
transfers with improved technique with decreased cueing and assistance required.
Assessment Summary Since Eval/SOC
Response to Tx Progress & Response to Tx: Pt. has made fair progress toward short term and long term PT goals over the last 10
visits of OP PT and I anticipate the Pt. will meet all PT goals by the end of the plan of care. Pt. has had difficulty
participating in skilled PT at times secondar to symptoms associated with A-fib and side effects from medications,
however Pt. is motivated to participate and progress toward PT goals. Pt. demonstrates improving static and dynamic
standing balance with the ability to ambulate on even and uneven surfaces with improved confidence and less loss of
balance with an improved TUG test score. Also, Pt. demonstrates improving LE strength and stability which has
contributed to improved transfers, gait, and stair climbing. Pt. demonstrates improving gait speed at 2.5 ft./sec.,
making the Pt. a limited community ambulator progressing toward full community ambulator status at >2.6 ft./sec.
Finally, Pt. demonstrates improving physiologic reserve/endurance with an improved 6 min. walk test score of 450 ft.
and the ability to ambulate indoors on even surfaces with decreased fatigue.
