Assessment Summary
Clinical Clinical Impressions: Based on direct OT observation of ADLs/fxl mobility, EMR review, patient report, and
Impressions standardized assessments pt demonstrates deficits related to balance, activity tolerance, and functional mobility.
These areas of deficit directly affect their ability to complete ADLs/fxl mobility at their PLOF. Skilled OT indicated to
max fxl (I) and return to PLOF. Pt is at risk for injury and/or flx decline without skilled intervention.
Reason for Skill Skilled Justification: Pt demonstrates areas of deficit related to balance, safety awareness, transfers, and posture.
This impacts their ability to engage in self care, functional mobility, hobbies, and leisure activities at a safe/optimal
level. Pt requies continuation of skilled OT intervention to optimize CLOF, prevent functional decline, and reduce the
risk of injury to ensure QOL for the patient.
