scale to determine their level of independence at evaluation and discharge. The MBI focuses on ten essential ADLs,
including bowel and bladder control, grooming, toilet use, feeding, transfers, walking, dressing, stair climbing, and
bathing. Pt scored 30 indicating severe dependence on caregivers to complete ADLs w deficts in bathing, walking,
dressing, stair climbing, and transfers
