Objective Tests and Measures
SLUMS SLUMS = 10; Score Interpretation: SLUMS:
Examination (SLUMS) was used to obtain information regarding this patient's cognitive
abilities. The SLUMS consists of 10 questions that assess delayed recall, verbal fluency,
comprehension, calculations, attention, working memory and orientation. A score is
calculated from a possible 30 points. Scores fall in one of three ranges describing the
patient's level of impairment based upon level of education. Patients who have completed
high school should would be expected to score slightly higher on this test than those who
have not.
