Initial Assessment / Current Level of Function & Underlying Impairments
Patient Referral and History
Current Referral Reason for Referral: Pt referred to to due to new onset of decrease in cognition, strength, functional mobility, R
shoulder pain, and overall functional decline.
Hx/Complexities Current Hx/Problem: Pt reports she was hospitalized severla months ago when she had “uncontrollable diarrhea”. Pt
reports a history of falls, trouble remembering dates, carpal tunnel in her R hand, R shoulder pain due to OA, and
history of CVA, with L leg becing the most affected. After her CVA she moved into Morning Star Arvada (January
2025). She has lost 30 pounds since being at Morning Star due to being a vegetarian and not finding an adequate
substitution on the menu. She has a history of chronic pain due to scolosis, needing a R shoulder joint replacement,
and carpal tunnel.
Prior Medical History: PMH includes OA, history of falls and Pt is in need of R shoulder replacement. Pt is a poor
histroian but reports having a stroke in Decemeber 2024. Pt had a recent hospitial stay in may from diarrhea. She
reports having lost a lot of weight since living here because she’s a vegetarian. She reports L side weakness following
her stoke. She had R side carpal tunnel.
Medical Precautions: Fall risk, cognitive impairments
