Objective Tests and Measures
SLUMS SLUMS = 17; Score Interpretation: SLUMS administer to obtain information regarding patient’s cognitive abilities. This
tool consists of questions that assess delayed recall, verbal fluency, comprehension, calculations, attention, working
memory, and orientation. A total score is calculated out of 30 possible points, with ranges indicating the patient’s level
of cognitive function based on education level: normal, mild cognitive impairment, or dementia.
SLUMS was completed this date. Subtest scores are as follows:
? Orientation: 2/3
? Immediate Recall: 3/5 (not calculated in total score)
