deficits result in limitations with mobility, self-care, and social engagement. Skilled OT services are indicated to
assess safety and independence with ADLs, maximize rehabilitation potential, and minimize safety hazards and
environmental barriers, supporting the patient’s ability to live with the least amount of supervision and assistance.
