Orders of Discipline and Treatments:
INSERT INDWELLING URINARY CATHETER PER PHYSICIAN ORDER 18 FR, WITH 10 CC BALLOON, MAY IRRIGATE WITH STERILE WATER AS
NEEDED FOR PATENCY, SECURE WITH SECUREMENT DEVICE AND CHANGE INDWELLING URINARY CATHETER EVERY MONTH OR AS
NEEDED FOR DISLODGEMENT, LEAKING, OR BLOCKAGEASSESS PATIENT FOR S/S OF URINARY INFECTIONEDUCATE
PATIENT/CAREGIVERS REGARDING CARE OF FOLEY CATHETER INCLUDING: CLEAN AWAY FROM PT AND KEEP BAG LOWER THAN
BODYEDUCATE PATIENT/CAREGIVER ON S&S OF INFECTION AND INSTRUCT TO NOTIFY HOSPICE IF NOTED
THE LICENSED PROFESSIONAL WHOSE SIGNATURE APPEARS IN BLOCK 23 ATTESTS THAT THE PHYSICIAN'S ORDERS WERE RECEIVED ON
9/22/2025.
Goals:
HOSPICE AIDE SERVICES: PATIENT PERSONAL CARE NEEDS WILL BE MET AEB HOSPICE AIDE ASSISTANCE WITH ADLS AND PERSONAL
CARE NEEDS
CHAPLAIN PLAN OF CARE WILL BE ESTABLISHED THAT MEETS THE PATIENT NEEDS AND WILL BE REVIEWED/UPDATED WITH THE IDG AT
MINIMUM OF EVERY 15 DAYS
MEDICAL SOCIAL WORKER PLAN OF CARE WILL BE ESTABLISHED THAT MEETS THE PATIENT NEEDS AND WILL BE REVIEWED/UPDATED
WITH THE IDG AT MINIMUM OF EVERY 15 DAYS
EDEMA WILL BE OPTIMALLY MANAGED AEB DECREASED S&S OF FLUID OVERLOAD WHILE ON HOSPICE SERVICES
HOSPICE NURSE PROVIDES ONGOING COMMUNICATION AND COLLABORATION WITH FACILITY STAFF AT HIGHLINE MEMORY CARE TO
ENSURE OPTIMAL PATIENT CARE THROUGHOUT HOSPICE SERVICES
CAREGIVER WILL IMPLEMENT MEASURES TO REDUCE RISK OF FALLS OR REMOVAL OF ENVIRONMENTAL HAZARDS AEB PATIENT
REMAINING FREE FROM FALLS OR INJURY THROUGHOUT HOSPICE SERVICES
PATIENT/CAREGIVER WILL UTILIZE MOBILITY ASSISTIVE DEVICES SAFELY AEB RETURN TEACH BACK DEMONSTRATION AND NO INJURY,
HARM, OR FALLS THROUGHOUT HOSPICE SERVICES
PAIN IS MANAGED AT OR BELOW ACCEPTABLE RATING OF MILD AS PATIENT IS ABLE TO VERBALLY REPORT WHILE ON HOSPICE SERVICES
PATIENT/FAMILY WILL UNDERSTAND AND TEACH BACK HOW TO EFFECTIVELY MANAGE PAIN AND TO REPORT CHANGES TO HOSPICE
PATIENT/CAREGIVER WILL VERBALIZE UNDERSTANDING OF POTENTIAL CAUSES OF SKIN BREAKDOWN AND PREVENTION MEASURES AEB
NO SKIN BREAKDOWN WHILE PATIENT IS ON HOSPICE SERVICES
CAREGIVER WILL VERBALIZE ADEQUATE KNOWLEDGE REQUIRED TO MANAGE INDWELLING CATHETER AEB PATENCY OF CATHETER AND
NO S/S OF INFECTION
DME and Supplies:
BRIEFS/BLADDER CONTROL PADS; DME-HOSPITAL BED ; DME-OVER THE BED TABLE; DME-SHOWER CHAIR; DME-WALKER ; DME-
WHEELCHAIR-HIGH BACK; DRESSING-WOUNDCARE; GLOVES ; INCONTINENCE SUPPLIES; NEBULIZER; SHAMPOO/BODYWASH; SKIN CARE
PRODUCTS; SKIN PROTECTANT; WOUND CLEANSER
Functional Limitations:
BOWEL/BLADDER (INCONTINENCE); ENDURANCE; AMBULATION
Safety Measures:
BEDBOUND PRECAUTIONS, CLEAR PATHWAYS, DYSPHAGIA PRECAUTIONS, EMERGENCY PLAN, FALL PRECAUTIONS, INFECTION
PRECAUTIONS, MEDICATION PRECAUTION, PAIN MGMT, STANDARD PRECAUTIONS
